# Common Interview Questions

### Q1

Difference between:

```sql
COUNT(*)
```

and

```sql
COUNT(column_name)
```

Example:

| salary |
| -----: |
|   5000 |
|   NULL |
|   6000 |

`COUNT(*)`

Result

```text
3
```

Counts all rows.

`COUNT(salary)`

Result

```text
2
```

Ignores `NULL`.

---

### Q2

Difference between

```sql
COUNT(*)
```

and

```sql
COUNT(DISTINCT department)
```

If departments are:

```text
IT
HR
IT
Finance
```

`COUNT(*)`

```text
4
```

`COUNT(DISTINCT department)`

```text
3
```

